data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code directly:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression-tree construction code won't compile. Replace it with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The `Action<...>` signature means you can use normal imperative code — no more `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` machinery.

---

### 2. Complex type column names are now uniquified/use full paths

Two changes combine here:

- **Duplicate property names** across complex types (e.g., `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) get a numeric suffix appended automatically.
- **Nested complex types** use the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

Both generate rename migrations. **Fix:** pin the old names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress, a =>
        {
            a.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method (`CommandReaderExecuting`, `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) now has an additional `string logCommandText` parameter. Your class won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ← new parameter (redacted SQL)
    { /* logging — use logCommandText for safe log output */ }
}
```

`logCommandText` contains a redacted version of the SQL (constants may be masked). Use it for logging; use `command.CommandText` for the actual SQL.
